The flexible printed circuit board market is expected to witness significant growth in the coming years due to the increasing demand for compact and lightweight electronic devices across various industries. The type segment is anticipated to register substantial growth, with the multi-layer segment expected to dominate the market as it offers enhanced functionality and performance compared to single-sided and double-sided PCBs. The automotive industry is projected to hold a significant market share in the end-user industry segment, driven by the growing adoption of flexible PCBs in advanced driver assistance systems and infotainment systems in vehicles. Additionally, the healthcare sector is likely to witness a surge in demand for flexible PCBs for medical devices and equipment, contributing to market growth.

In the application segment, the display segment is poised to experience rapid growth, fueled by the increasing deployment of flexible displays in smartphones, tablets, and wearable devices. The automotive application segment is also set to expand significantly as automotive manufacturers integrate flexible PCBs in advanced electronics systems for vehicles. Moreover, the LED segment is expected to grow steadily as the demand for energy-efficient lighting solutions rises globally.

